Definition: a deep feeling of guilt often experienced by those who have survived some catastrophe that took the lives of many others
Example: derives in part from a feeling that they did not do enough to save the others who perished and in part from feelings of being unworthy relative to those who died; survivor guilt was first noted in those who survived the Holocaust
Synonyms: guilt, noun, state, posttraumatic_stress_disorder, p, a, deep, feeling, of, often, experienced, by, those, who, have, survived, some, catastrophe, that, took, the, lives, many, others, derives, in, part, from, they, did, not, do, enough, to, save, perished, and, feelings, being, unworthy, relative, died, survivor, was, first, noted, Holocaust
Category: noun.feeling
